mcqs.question:
Consider the following CUDA kernel for vector addition:

__global__ void add(float *a, float *b, float *c, int n) {
    int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
    if (i < n) c[i] = a[i] + b[i];
}

If this kernel is launched with gridDim=1 and blockDim=64 for n=100, how many elements of c will be correctly computed?
